The [[Same-origin Policy]] is a concept in the web application [[Security Model]], under which a web browser permits scripts contained in a first web page to access data in a second web page __only if__ both web pages have the same [[Origin|Origin (HTTP)]].

Note that the [[Same-origin Policy]] applies only to scripts - so attackers can still exploit [[HTML Tags]].